.TH PAI-STATUS 1 "April 2026" "PAI" "PAI User Commands"
.SH NAME
pai-status \- report PAI privacy and system status
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pai-status
.RI [ --json | --brief | -h | --help ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B pai-status
is a one-shot command that answers \(lqam I private right now?\(rq on a
running PAI system. It inspects the local Ollama daemon, memory usage,
listening and outbound network sockets, firewall posture, MAC address
spoofing, persistence state, and Tor status, and prints a summary
suitable for quick inspection or for a status bar.
.PP
The same data backs the Waybar applet and the forthcoming GTK
dashboard, so what the CLI reports is what the GUI reports.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --json
Emit structured JSON. Intended for Waybar custom modules, dashboards,
and scripts. The shape is stable across releases within a major
version.
.TP
.B --brief
One-line summary suitable for a status bar or prompt.
.TP
.BR -h ", " --help
Print usage and exit.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Status printed; private-mode defaults are healthy.
.TP
.B 1
A problem was detected (e.g. service down, firewall open, unexpected
outbound connection).
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/pai-status
The executable.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR pai-recommend-model (1),
.BR pai-models (1),
.BR ollama (1)
.SH AUTHOR
The PAI project \[em] https://pai.direct
